txt.en: 'Ye have to be careful hereabouts...been a lot o' rough strangers coming through town.'
'Cousin o' mine wandered into the Old Forest when we was little. He came out white as a sheet.'
'Are ye one o' them raggedy folk from the south or, worse yet, one o' them Rangers?'
'I told Adso that setting shop up on the East Road's a fool's errand, but there's nothing for it now.'
